WEBVTT

1
00:01:22.605 --> 00:01:24.653
Did you lie to me?

2
00:01:25.911 --> 00:01:28.192
I didn't lie.

3
00:01:29.586 --> 00:01:31.833
So what was it?

4
00:01:35.986 --> 00:01:37.500
It's just...

5
00:01:39.500 --> 00:01:42.159
I was trying to find the right moment.

6
00:01:48.928 --> 00:01:50.427
Were you ever going to tell me

7
00:01:50.427 --> 00:01:52.003
or were you going to keep lying?

8
00:01:52.003 --> 00:01:54.573
If I tried to hide it, I wouldn't have told you.

9
00:01:54.573 --> 00:01:57.190
So it wasn't the right time?

10
00:01:57.190 --> 00:01:58.710
I did not mean that.

11
00:01:58.710 --> 00:02:00.736
So what do you mean?

12
00:02:00.736 --> 00:02:02.953
You say you don't have a son?

13
00:02:09.550 --> 00:02:11.816
Did it seem that easy to you?

14
00:02:13.431 --> 00:02:15.399
Did you think I was so alone

15
00:02:15.399 --> 00:02:18.712
I wouldn't mind if you had a child?

16
00:02:20.070 --> 00:02:21.650
Anything else you want to confess?

17
00:02:21.650 --> 00:02:23.290
Any criminal record?

18
00:02:23.290 --> 00:02:25.856
I was afraid you would react like that...

19
00:02:27.582 --> 00:02:29.962
That's why it was difficult for me to tell you.

20
00:02:42.818 --> 00:02:44.884
I was afraid...

21
00:02:50.236 --> 00:02:52.323
because I like you a lot.

22
00:03:00.273 --> 00:03:02.573
How do you think that makes me feel?

23
00:03:03.640 --> 00:03:04.885
I hate myself for loving you,

24
00:03:04.885 --> 00:03:06.738
for trusting someone like you.

25
00:03:06.738 --> 00:03:08.924
I regret it a lot.

26
00:03:27.974 --> 00:03:29.253
[Do Hyun]

27
00:03:29.253 --> 00:03:31.754
<i>I'll stop by this weekend to get my things.</i>

28
00:03:33.360 --> 00:03:37.033
<i>If it makes you uncomfortable, I will come when you are not at home.</i>

29
00:04:02.806 --> 00:04:05.032
[Idiot]

30
00:04:05.032 --> 00:04:06.877
- Hello.
<i>- Where are you?</i>

31
00:04:06.877 --> 00:04:09.370
- At home.
<i>- What are you doing?</i>

32
00:04:09.370 --> 00:04:11.663
I have an existential crisis.

33
00:04:11.663 --> 00:04:15.923
Some create masterpieces at 18,

34
00:04:15.923 --> 00:04:17.410
and others

35
00:04:17.410 --> 00:04:20.107
they are 27
and correct typographical errors of others.

36
00:04:20.107 --> 00:04:21.305
I'm going there.

37
00:04:21.305 --> 00:04:23.228
<i>I just showered and changed.</i>

38
00:04:23.228 --> 00:04:25.874
So what? Just wait for me.

39
00:04:59.313 --> 00:05:01.207
- Know?
- That?

40
00:05:01.207 --> 00:05:03.445
You don't usually try that hard in life.

41
00:05:03.445 --> 00:05:07.093
Don't start, just read it.

42
00:05:07.093 --> 00:05:11.340
Do graduate students
Do they always write such long essays?

43
00:05:11.340 --> 00:05:13.053
Is it too much?

44
00:05:13.659 --> 00:05:15.265
There is a saying:

45
00:05:15.265 --> 00:05:17.123
"I didn't have time to write a short letter,

46
00:05:17.123 --> 00:05:19.616
so I wrote a long one."

47
00:05:19.616 --> 00:05:21.776
It's by Mark Twain.

48
00:05:21.776 --> 00:05:23.336
See?

49
00:05:23.336 --> 00:05:24.841
The longer it is,

50
00:05:24.841 --> 00:05:27.140
more it shows that you are not ready.

51
00:05:27.140 --> 00:05:28.886
So help me adjust it,

52
00:05:28.886 --> 00:05:31.912
to make it precise and irrefutable.

53
00:05:33.026 --> 00:05:35.552
let me benefit
of the future great writer.

54
00:05:36.773 --> 00:05:38.406
Good.

55
00:05:39.615 --> 00:05:41.623
That smells amazing.

56
00:05:41.623 --> 00:05:43.235
It's crazy.

57
00:05:56.691 --> 00:05:57.716
It's delicious, right?

58
00:05:57.716 --> 00:06:00.361
My parents returned to the field for their garden,

59
00:06:00.361 --> 00:06:02.726
so I basically lived in your house
and I ate all your food.

60
00:06:02.726 --> 00:06:05.256
Yes, I told you to move.

61
00:06:05.256 --> 00:06:06.802
Clear.

62
00:06:16.759 --> 00:06:20.058
Your mom's kimchi fried rice
was the best.

63
00:06:21.852 --> 00:06:23.505
Hey,

64
00:06:24.445 --> 00:06:26.332
what's wrong with you?

65
00:06:28.220 --> 00:06:30.333
I just miss your mom.

66
00:06:35.594 --> 00:06:37.333
I'm sorry.

67
00:06:42.308 --> 00:06:44.094
Still, it feels good,

68
00:06:45.109 --> 00:06:47.448
because I can talk about my mother.

69
00:06:49.586 --> 00:06:52.159
If I had known that he would leave so suddenly,

70
00:06:53.225 --> 00:06:55.639
I would have tried harder

71
00:06:55.639 --> 00:06:58.192
to become someone sooner.

72
00:06:59.519 --> 00:07:01.225
It's a real shame.

73
00:08:20.163 --> 00:08:23.572
[Listen 25 Minimarket]

74
00:08:23.572 --> 00:08:25.584
It seems the power went out.

75
00:08:25.584 --> 00:08:27.105
Do you have cash?

76
00:08:27.105 --> 00:08:29.292
No.

77
00:08:42.004 --> 00:08:44.183
I don't have cash either.

78
00:08:45.237 --> 00:08:46.494
I'll return this and leave.

79
00:08:46.494 --> 00:08:48.607
No, I'll take care of it.

80
00:08:48.607 --> 00:08:50.760
Why is there no light?

81
00:08:50.760 --> 00:08:52.827
Why is it so dark here?

82
00:08:54.106 --> 00:08:55.867
Give me a pack of cigarettes.

83
00:08:55.867 --> 00:08:58.365
Sorry, the power went out.

84
00:08:58.365 --> 00:09:00.390
Do you have cash?

85
00:09:00.390 --> 00:09:03.097
Who carries cash nowadays?

86
00:09:03.777 --> 00:09:07.144
The box doesn't work,
so the cards are useless.

87
00:09:07.144 --> 00:09:09.153
Now you disrespect me?

88
00:09:09.153 --> 00:09:11.144
Do you look down on me?

89
00:09:11.144 --> 00:09:13.022
What are you taking about?

90
00:09:13.022 --> 00:09:16.438
He said the cards don't work
because of the blackout.

91
00:09:16.438 --> 00:09:18.679
Who the hell are you?

92
00:09:21.301 --> 00:09:23.740
-And who the hell are you?
- That?

93
00:09:23.740 --> 00:09:25.429
How dare they?

94
00:09:25.429 --> 00:09:26.939
You two...

95
00:09:32.395 --> 00:09:34.714
Give me the cigarettes now!

96
00:09:34.714 --> 00:09:35.992
Yes sir.

97
00:09:35.992 --> 00:09:37.292
What are you looking at?

98
00:09:37.292 --> 00:09:39.625
Police? I'm in a store
in the Yeonhwa neighborhood.

99
00:09:39.625 --> 00:09:41.661
There's a drunk here.

100
00:09:43.701 --> 00:09:46.600
He throws things and threatens us.

101
00:09:46.600 --> 00:09:48.380
Please come immediately.

102
00:10:02.069 --> 00:10:05.356
It seems that the entire area is in darkness.

103
00:10:05.356 --> 00:10:08.743
My boss told us to close
until the light came back.

104
00:10:08.743 --> 00:10:11.169
I can't serve customers,

105
00:10:11.169 --> 00:10:13.962
just in case
that things get out of control.

106
00:10:16.734 --> 00:10:18.388
Thank you.

107
00:10:21.520 --> 00:10:23.553
You can close the door.

108
00:10:39.442 --> 00:10:41.564
Do you want me to stay with you?

109
00:10:49.929 --> 00:10:53.022
If I go home, it will be dark too,

110
00:10:54.142 --> 00:10:56.002
and I don't even have candles.

111
00:11:06.193 --> 00:11:09.660
<i>Those who listen to "Night Walk"
They have known it for a while:</i>

112
00:11:09.660 --> 00:11:12.118
<i>I love cherry blossoms.</i>

113
00:11:12.118 --> 00:11:13.731
You hear this, right?

114
00:11:15.000 --> 00:11:18.620
<i>Spring
It came especially late this year.</i>

115
00:11:18.620 --> 00:11:21.553
<i>I heard that the flowers would open late too,</i>

116
00:11:21.553 --> 00:11:23.784
<i>so I waited and waited</i>

117
00:11:23.784 --> 00:11:26.466
<i>in the hope of seeing them in full bloom,</i>

118
00:11:26.466 --> 00:11:29.926
<i>but a sudden rain
He made them fall before their time.</i>

119
00:11:30.756 --> 00:11:32.732
<i>In the end, I missed them.</i>

120
00:11:36.709 --> 00:11:40.729
<i>Why do good things
Do they disappear so quickly?</i>

121
00:12:05.606 --> 00:12:07.930
How did he hide that he had a son?

122
00:12:07.930 --> 00:12:11.669
One becomes two,
and suddenly there are variables.

123
00:12:11.669 --> 00:12:13.030
No, actually there are three.

124
00:12:13.030 --> 00:12:15.850
Do you find it funny?

125
00:12:15.850 --> 00:12:18.316
At least he's not married.

126
00:12:18.316 --> 00:12:20.689
And if he stays alone at Jun Kyung's house,

127
00:12:20.689 --> 00:12:22.337
You are not raising your child.

128
00:12:22.337 --> 00:12:24.123
What is the problem?

129
00:12:24.123 --> 00:12:26.403
He's divorced, right?

130
00:12:26.403 --> 00:12:28.411
- How old is the child?
- Enough.

131
00:12:28.411 --> 00:12:29.963
What does that matter now?

132
00:12:29.963 --> 00:12:32.403
Anyway, delete his number.

133
00:12:32.403 --> 00:12:35.316
If you save it, you will wait for me to call you

134
00:12:35.316 --> 00:12:37.930
and you will end up calling him when you feel alone.

135
00:12:37.930 --> 00:12:39.330
I already deleted it.

136
00:12:39.330 --> 00:12:41.516
You probably memorized it.

137
00:12:41.516 --> 00:12:44.176
Erase it from your head too.

138
00:12:46.449 --> 00:12:47.639
You need a drink.

139
00:12:47.639 --> 00:12:49.403
Drink and forget everything.

140
00:12:49.403 --> 00:12:51.231
Let's drink.

141
00:12:53.418 --> 00:12:54.980
Are you really going to break up with him?

142
00:12:54.980 --> 00:12:56.586
In fact, we're done.

143
00:12:56.586 --> 00:12:58.793
Didn't you hear he has a son?

144
00:12:58.793 --> 00:13:02.733
What better reason to break up?

145
00:13:04.908 --> 00:13:06.408
Let's go...

146
00:13:06.408 --> 00:13:10.384
It's like you always wait
a reason to leave.

147
00:13:10.384 --> 00:13:11.840
Did you hear his version?

148
00:13:11.840 --> 00:13:13.814
The reason I didn't tell you?

149
00:13:15.793 --> 00:13:18.473
Hey, you still love him, right?

150
00:13:18.473 --> 00:13:21.666
Isn't that a very strong reason to continue?

151
00:13:26.361 --> 00:13:27.634
- Who is it?
- Hey,

152
00:13:27.634 --> 00:13:29.481
don't answer

153
00:13:29.481 --> 00:13:31.881
It's not Do Hyun.

154
00:13:31.881 --> 00:13:35.214
You don't need to remember
the number of a scammer.

155
00:13:35.214 --> 00:13:36.867
Hello?

156
00:13:38.553 --> 00:13:40.047
Yeah.

157
00:13:42.393 --> 00:13:43.911
At first,

158
00:13:43.911 --> 00:13:47.211
this space asked for it
a terminally ill father.

159
00:13:47.211 --> 00:13:49.341
His family paid a deposit for months

160
00:13:49.341 --> 00:13:51.414
to reserve it specifically.

161
00:13:52.134 --> 00:13:53.538
There was an error on the part of our staff.

162
00:13:53.538 --> 00:13:55.911
We sincerely apologize.

163
00:13:55.911 --> 00:13:58.900
How could something like this happen?

164
00:13:58.900 --> 00:14:00.866
I don't understand.

165
00:14:00.866 --> 00:14:03.679
We were surprised too
when we found out.

166
00:14:03.679 --> 00:14:04.960
Were you surprised?

167
00:14:04.960 --> 00:14:07.480
Do you think this is like canceling
a reservation at a restaurant?

168
00:14:07.480 --> 00:14:09.140
We have nothing more to say.

169
00:14:09.140 --> 00:14:10.853
That's all?

170
00:14:12.100 --> 00:14:14.873
Once again,
We offer you our most sincere apologies.

171
00:14:14.873 --> 00:14:18.526
Do you think an apology will fix this?

172
00:14:20.293 --> 00:14:22.613
So is there any space left?

173
00:14:22.613 --> 00:14:24.379
Yes. Please follow me.

174
00:14:27.540 --> 00:14:29.313
Here.

175
00:14:42.634 --> 00:14:45.158
Thank you all for this great day.

176
00:14:45.158 --> 00:14:47.831
Yes, thanks!

177
00:14:47.831 --> 00:14:50.636
We will return to our hotels and rest,

178
00:14:50.636 --> 00:14:53.049
and then we'll see each other tonight
dressed in our best clothes.

179
00:14:53.049 --> 00:14:54.299
- OK.
- See you.

180
00:14:54.299 --> 00:14:55.667
- See you tonight.
- Thank you.

181
00:14:55.667 --> 00:14:56.833
Let them rest.

182
00:14:56.833 --> 00:14:59.339
Jun Kyung, how are you?

183
00:15:00.203 --> 00:15:01.663
Good.

184
00:15:01.663 --> 00:15:04.270
How are you, dad?

185
00:15:04.270 --> 00:15:06.970
It's nice here.

186
00:15:06.970 --> 00:15:09.329
Good weather, breeze, sea.

187
00:15:09.329 --> 00:15:10.876
And you?

188
00:15:14.025 --> 00:15:16.590
Now I'm at home with Jun Seo.

189
00:15:16.590 --> 00:15:17.855
<i>Yes?</i>

190
00:15:17.855 --> 00:15:19.285
<i>That's very good.</i>

191
00:15:19.285 --> 00:15:21.351
<i>So, are you going to have dinner together?</i>

192
00:15:25.480 --> 00:15:27.563
Wait, dad...

193
00:15:27.563 --> 00:15:29.196
<i>Yes?</i>

194
00:15:29.196 --> 00:15:30.943
Wait a second.

195
00:15:36.148 --> 00:15:38.448
- Dad?
- Hello, Jun Seo.

196
00:15:38.448 --> 00:15:40.850
I felt bad for leaving without seeing you,

197
00:15:40.850 --> 00:15:43.888
<i>but hearing your voice like that makes me feel better.</i>

198
00:15:45.437 --> 00:15:47.564
- Dad.
<i>- Yes?</i>

199
00:15:51.638 --> 00:15:53.444
I'm sorry for what happened earlier.

200
00:15:54.218 --> 00:15:56.030
Have a good time.

201
00:16:05.139 --> 00:16:08.573
We don't want to ruin your day, do we?

202
00:16:14.985 --> 00:16:16.904
- Come on?
- Yes.

203
00:16:16.904 --> 00:16:19.743
They call just to see how I am,
even when nothing happens.

204
00:16:19.743 --> 00:16:22.276
It is usually the parents
those who worry like this.

205
00:16:22.276 --> 00:16:24.690
Now that they've grown up,
They are the ones who care about me.

206
00:16:24.690 --> 00:16:26.950
Looks like your kids turned out okay.

207
00:16:26.950 --> 00:16:28.696
Yeah.

208
00:16:28.696 --> 00:16:30.756
My daughter is an obstetrician and gynecologist,

209
00:16:30.756 --> 00:16:32.856
and my son is doing graduate school.

210
00:16:32.856 --> 00:16:34.962
They are very friendly.

211
00:16:34.962 --> 00:16:36.207
You must be proud.

212
00:16:36.207 --> 00:16:38.016
But it's not that simple.

213
00:16:38.016 --> 00:16:40.275
My son has not yet found
what you love to do,

214
00:16:40.275 --> 00:16:42.489
and that worries me.

215
00:16:42.489 --> 00:16:44.362
My daughter still hasn't found someone to love,

216
00:16:44.362 --> 00:16:46.395
and that worries me too.

217
00:16:49.530 --> 00:16:51.469
When did we take that photo?

218
00:16:52.789 --> 00:16:55.150
Was it the year you started college?

219
00:16:55.150 --> 00:16:57.523
It was my orientation day.

220
00:17:00.703 --> 00:17:03.150
A few months before mom's accident.

221
00:17:04.955 --> 00:17:06.882
We look very uncomfortable.

222
00:17:08.056 --> 00:17:10.515
Why were we smiling like that?

223
00:18:11.661 --> 00:18:13.401
You look...

224
00:18:17.385 --> 00:18:19.409
very good.

225
00:18:22.869 --> 00:18:24.582
Dear?

226
00:18:27.136 --> 00:18:30.189
Know? In retrospect,

227
00:18:30.189 --> 00:18:34.189
Our family was not so happy,
Even before mom's accident,

228
00:18:35.522 --> 00:18:38.035
but we weren't unhappy either.

229
00:18:41.930 --> 00:18:43.570
Do you think so?

230
00:18:45.970 --> 00:18:47.583
Of course.

231
00:18:47.583 --> 00:18:49.363
We were normal.

232
00:18:50.863 --> 00:18:52.453
We...

233
00:18:57.783 --> 00:18:59.556
No, I...

234
00:19:01.727 --> 00:19:05.360
I think I blamed mom for my unhappiness.

235
00:19:06.316 --> 00:19:08.335
It was my fault.

236
00:19:14.109 --> 00:19:17.330
Gosh, the power went out again.

237
00:19:17.330 --> 00:19:19.172
- Hey.
- Yeah?

238
00:19:21.510 --> 00:19:24.710
Do you think this has happened
when mom was alone?

239
00:19:48.026 --> 00:19:50.122
<i>He must have been scared.</i>

240
00:19:51.454 --> 00:19:53.693
<i>Yes.</i>

241
00:19:53.693 --> 00:19:55.666
<i>She probably felt lonely too.</i>

242
00:20:04.515 --> 00:20:05.799
<i>Honey,</i>

243
00:20:05.799 --> 00:20:08.012
<i>why are you in the dark?</i>

244
00:20:13.313 --> 00:20:15.686
<i>I understand, the power went out.</i>

245
00:20:21.575 --> 00:20:23.210
<i>Ready.</i>

246
00:20:23.210 --> 00:20:25.385
<i>Now there is light.</i>

247
00:20:25.385 --> 00:20:28.818
<i>Next time the power goes out, go there...</i>

248
00:20:34.459 --> 00:20:35.917
<i>Honey.</i>

249
00:20:38.258 --> 00:20:39.360
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

250
00:20:39.360 --> 00:20:42.026
<i>I shouldn't have said that, I'm sorry.</i>

251
00:20:44.282 --> 00:20:46.156
<i>Don't cry.</i>

252
00:20:48.222 --> 00:20:50.362
<i>You were afraid, right?</i>

253
00:20:51.556 --> 00:20:52.930
<i>I'm very sorry.</i>

254
00:20:52.930 --> 00:20:54.650
<i>I'm sorry I came home late.</i>

255
00:20:54.650 --> 00:20:56.536
<i>Honey, don't cry.</i>

256
00:21:18.296 --> 00:21:21.075
It wasn't late.

257
00:21:21.075 --> 00:21:22.860
I always had you

258
00:21:22.860 --> 00:21:25.330
at my side

259
00:21:25.330 --> 00:21:28.670
That's why I felt sorry

260
00:21:29.725 --> 00:21:32.976
and gratitude every day.

261
00:21:32.976 --> 00:21:36.016
- Dear.
- Don't cry,

262
00:21:36.016 --> 00:21:38.709
everyone is waiting for you outside.

263
00:21:42.116 --> 00:21:44.156
you look

264
00:21:44.156 --> 00:21:46.409
amazing today.

265
00:21:46.409 --> 00:21:47.809
That?

266
00:21:48.649 --> 00:21:52.536
That woman, Ja Yeong,

267
00:21:52.536 --> 00:21:54.670
It's pretty.

268
00:21:54.670 --> 00:21:56.762
It looks good on you.

269
00:21:57.490 --> 00:22:00.569
Don't say that.

270
00:22:00.569 --> 00:22:04.729
Don't hesitate anymore, don't hold back.

271
00:22:05.930 --> 00:22:07.570
you should think

272
00:22:08.389 --> 00:22:11.263
in you

273
00:22:11.263 --> 00:22:14.070
and live for you.

274
00:22:14.796 --> 00:22:19.736
I want you to be truly happy.

275
00:22:19.736 --> 00:22:21.483
OK.

276
00:22:21.483 --> 00:22:24.650
Every day,

277
00:22:24.650 --> 00:22:26.316
be happy.

278
00:22:28.990 --> 00:22:31.182
Dear.

279
00:22:32.455 --> 00:22:34.183
Dear.

280
00:22:34.183 --> 00:22:36.110
Dear.

281
00:22:36.110 --> 00:22:38.785
Dear!

282
00:22:40.446 --> 00:22:42.512
Dear.

283
00:23:07.168 --> 00:23:08.358
- Sorry.
- Yeah?

284
00:23:08.358 --> 00:23:12.660
Is there a tall and thin man
middle-aged inside?

285
00:23:12.660 --> 00:23:14.281
There is no one.

286
00:23:20.393 --> 00:23:22.139
Mr. Seo Jin Ho?

287
00:23:26.047 --> 00:23:27.533
Mr. Seo Jin Ho?

288
00:23:30.413 --> 00:23:31.919
Mr. Seo?

289
00:23:56.442 --> 00:23:58.638
What are you doing here?

290
00:24:01.136 --> 00:24:03.136
Did something happen?

291
00:24:08.453 --> 00:24:10.946
Maybe you don't understand

292
00:24:11.620 --> 00:24:13.653
why am I like this?

293
00:24:16.815 --> 00:24:19.588
I feel like I'm the only one who lives well...

294
00:24:21.352 --> 00:24:23.632
and that makes me feel very guilty.

295
00:24:25.639 --> 00:24:27.565
It hurts a lot.

296
00:24:28.160 --> 00:24:31.253
It would be stranger if you didn't feel that way.

297
00:24:32.926 --> 00:24:34.397
No.

298
00:24:36.304 --> 00:24:38.697
You already got over it.

299
00:24:38.697 --> 00:24:41.227
Someone weak like me,

300
00:24:41.227 --> 00:24:43.160
these feelings...

301
00:24:44.406 --> 00:24:46.279
You wouldn't understand.

302
00:24:47.926 --> 00:24:49.739
I understand you...

303
00:24:51.672 --> 00:24:53.865
more than anyone.

304
00:24:56.880 --> 00:25:01.546
<i>My husband was always busy and distant.</i>

305
00:25:02.913 --> 00:25:05.650
<i>When I felt sorry,</i>

306
00:25:05.650 --> 00:25:07.866
<i>he promised me that,</i>

307
00:25:07.866 --> 00:25:09.613
<i>when he retired,</i>

308
00:25:09.613 --> 00:25:12.093
<i>we would travel together
the pilgrimage path.</i>

309
00:25:13.382 --> 00:25:15.057
<i>But he</i>

310
00:25:15.911 --> 00:25:18.571
<i>he could never keep that promise.</i>

311
00:25:20.076 --> 00:25:22.176
<i>I thought about it for a long time.</i>

312
00:25:22.896 --> 00:25:25.703
<i>"What would it mean to go alone?"</i>

313
00:25:27.870 --> 00:25:29.529
<i>But in the end,</i>

314
00:25:30.216 --> 00:25:32.742
<i>I went alone,</i>

315
00:25:33.730 --> 00:25:35.436
<i>like you.</i>

316
00:25:52.112 --> 00:25:55.784
<i>Do you know what I packed when I left?</i>

317
00:26:00.390 --> 00:26:02.523
<i>For the last day of the pilgrimage,</i>

318
00:26:03.623 --> 00:26:05.530
<i>for that day...</i>

319
00:26:07.316 --> 00:26:10.569
<i>I went from hospital to hospital,</i>

320
00:26:12.036 --> 00:26:14.063
<i>gathering sleeping pills.</i>

321
00:26:37.843 --> 00:26:40.376
<i>I emptied the jar,</i>

322
00:26:41.896 --> 00:26:44.562
<i>I lay down and lay motionless in bed.</i>

323
00:26:45.523 --> 00:26:47.296
<i>And, suddenly,</i>

324
00:26:47.296 --> 00:26:49.863
<i>I felt very sorry for myself.</i>

325
00:27:13.481 --> 00:27:17.315
<i>It wasn't that I wanted to live for my husband.</i>

326
00:27:18.653 --> 00:27:20.726
<i>I felt very pathetic...</i>

327
00:27:23.707 --> 00:27:26.140
and my life was unbearably sad.

328
00:27:28.443 --> 00:27:30.849
The life I still had left...

329
00:27:33.041 --> 00:27:35.175
I was too valuable to give up.

330
00:27:45.842 --> 00:27:48.109
Thank you.

331
00:27:48.109 --> 00:27:50.235
It must have been difficult to talk about.

332
00:27:51.673 --> 00:27:53.286
I just wanted to say

333
00:27:54.053 --> 00:27:57.072
that your life is not over yet.

334
00:27:59.986 --> 00:28:02.320
They say life is a festival.

335
00:28:12.136 --> 00:28:15.076
Our festival is not over yet.

336
00:28:19.742 --> 00:28:21.649
Do you want to go out?

337
00:29:01.870 --> 00:29:04.243
For our latest song, we are accepting requests.

338
00:29:04.243 --> 00:29:05.400
If you have one...

339
00:29:05.400 --> 00:29:09.180
How about a song
What would your wife love?

340
00:29:14.047 --> 00:29:15.730
No.

341
00:29:16.367 --> 00:29:18.933
Let's ask for a song that you like.

342
00:29:22.770 --> 00:29:24.498
My name is Ja Yeong.

343
00:29:25.190 --> 00:29:26.798
Jin Ja Yeong.

344
00:29:31.030 --> 00:29:32.966
Very good, Ja Yeong.

345
00:29:35.283 --> 00:29:37.982
Let's listen together to a song that you like.

346
00:30:29.966 --> 00:30:31.979
<i>Aren't we exaggerating?</i>

347
00:30:33.259 --> 00:30:34.696
Come here to look for him?

348
00:30:34.696 --> 00:30:36.466
We are not usually this type of family.

349
00:30:36.466 --> 00:30:40.412
Dad must have felt very alone
traveling without company.

350
00:30:42.525 --> 00:30:44.418
Yes,

351
00:30:44.418 --> 00:30:46.685
It is probable.

352
00:30:49.033 --> 00:30:50.431
By the way,

353
00:30:50.431 --> 00:30:52.766
since when do you say the right thing?

354
00:30:54.173 --> 00:30:55.633
Yes, well,

355
00:30:55.633 --> 00:30:57.679
I guess your conscience is affecting you.

356
00:30:58.299 --> 00:31:00.806
You were busy
dating the guy next door, right?

357
00:31:01.480 --> 00:31:04.113
How long has it been?

358
00:31:08.230 --> 00:31:09.663
That?

359
00:31:09.663 --> 00:31:12.121
I was waiting for an answer. Why so quiet?

360
00:31:12.121 --> 00:31:13.923
The truth

361
00:31:14.663 --> 00:31:17.890
It's just that we don't treat each other well as a family.

362
00:31:18.507 --> 00:31:20.370
Let's try it.

363
00:31:20.370 --> 00:31:22.383
Silently, so that no one notices.

364
00:31:25.004 --> 00:31:27.216
Look, there's dad.

365
00:31:27.216 --> 00:31:29.254
Don't make a funny face, do it for him.

366
00:31:29.254 --> 00:31:31.074
Worry about yourself.

367
00:31:32.911 --> 00:31:36.384
Everyone in our group
They had strong personalities.

368
00:31:36.384 --> 00:31:37.884
Thanks to you,

369
00:31:37.884 --> 00:31:39.504
I had a great time.

370
00:31:39.504 --> 00:31:41.444
Me too.

371
00:31:41.444 --> 00:31:44.757
This journey will accompany me for a long time.

372
00:31:45.804 --> 00:31:47.890
- Dad!
- Over here!

373
00:31:49.944 --> 00:31:52.775
It looks good, doesn't it?

374
00:31:52.775 --> 00:31:56.308
He's probably holding on.

375
00:31:57.402 --> 00:31:59.454
Say hello well.

376
00:32:02.214 --> 00:32:04.522
Mr. Seo,

377
00:32:04.522 --> 00:32:07.328
It's time to wake up from oblivion.

378
00:32:16.740 --> 00:32:19.501
[Information document
about burial in trees]

379
00:32:19.501 --> 00:32:22.547
They say that even the urn will decompose there.

380
00:32:23.392 --> 00:32:26.454
Everything returns to earth.

381
00:32:26.454 --> 00:32:28.454
Isn't that a little strange?

382
00:32:31.761 --> 00:32:34.067
What do you think, dad?

383
00:32:46.958 --> 00:32:48.857
You haven't eaten yet, have you?

384
00:33:08.613 --> 00:33:10.566
Is something wrong?

385
00:33:15.117 --> 00:33:16.750
No.

386
00:33:20.004 --> 00:33:22.483
I know it may sound strange, but...

387
00:33:24.417 --> 00:33:26.441
mom passed away,

388
00:33:26.441 --> 00:33:28.841
and you ask if something happens?

389
00:33:29.703 --> 00:33:31.630
Isn't that a little strange?

390
00:33:47.308 --> 00:33:49.316
How about

391
00:33:49.316 --> 00:33:51.355
something spicy?

392
00:33:52.676 --> 00:33:54.749
Like what?

393
00:33:54.749 --> 00:33:56.989
Whatever they want.

394
00:33:58.487 --> 00:34:00.529
So,

395
00:34:00.529 --> 00:34:02.369
How about <i>tteokbokki</i>?

396
00:34:02.369 --> 00:34:04.422
Isn't it very spicy?

397
00:34:04.422 --> 00:34:06.255
You ask for it.

398
00:34:06.255 --> 00:34:08.180
I don't have my phone now. Can you order?

399
00:34:08.180 --> 00:34:11.111
[Julia, Kim Mi Ran]

400
00:34:11.111 --> 00:34:13.064
Well done, Jun Kyung.

401
00:34:14.209 --> 00:34:15.730
your mom

402
00:34:15.730 --> 00:34:18.396
I was stuck at home all the time.

403
00:34:19.429 --> 00:34:23.015
This open place suits you better.

404
00:34:25.878 --> 00:34:27.588
My sister has a tree now.

405
00:34:27.588 --> 00:34:30.412
My dear, I may not come often,

406
00:34:30.412 --> 00:34:31.869
but I will visit you when I can.

407
00:34:31.869 --> 00:34:33.842
Take care of yourself.

408
00:34:44.443 --> 00:34:47.079
- That's better.
- Yes.

409
00:34:47.079 --> 00:34:49.132
- It's cute.
- Yes.

410
00:34:51.039 --> 00:34:53.579
I feel really bad for his dad.

411
00:34:55.188 --> 00:34:58.941
I couldn't live without her.

412
00:34:58.941 --> 00:35:02.394
What if he does something reckless?

413
00:35:04.141 --> 00:35:07.041
Not only the dead deserve compassion.

414
00:35:07.808 --> 00:35:10.034
The living too.

415
00:35:11.735 --> 00:35:14.628
Take good care of your dad.

416
00:35:19.303 --> 00:35:20.536
Take care of yourself

417
00:35:20.536 --> 00:35:22.704
and stop getting drunk for no reason.

418
00:35:22.704 --> 00:35:24.988
- Come on.
-Have a drink with Jin Ho too.

419
00:35:24.988 --> 00:35:26.474
I will do that.

420
00:35:29.368 --> 00:35:33.361
<i>Don't forget the party tonight at six.</i>

421
00:35:58.243 --> 00:36:00.003
Hello.

422
00:36:00.003 --> 00:36:04.190
"Popularize Korean legends with AI"?

423
00:36:04.190 --> 00:36:06.063
It sounds boring.

424
00:36:10.488 --> 00:36:13.261
Do you want to hear something funny?

425
00:36:13.261 --> 00:36:14.684
You know Yuna, right?

426
00:36:14.684 --> 00:36:17.407
I'll do the choreography for your new song.

427
00:36:18.177 --> 00:36:20.163
Oh really?

428
00:36:20.163 --> 00:36:23.023
What if I become too famous?

429
00:36:23.023 --> 00:36:24.550
Yes.

430
00:36:29.597 --> 00:36:31.683
- You're annoying.
- What are you doing?

431
00:36:33.970 --> 00:36:35.174
TRUE.

432
00:36:35.174 --> 00:36:36.913
Whose choreography was it?

433
00:36:40.765 --> 00:36:42.711
It suits you perfectly.

434
00:36:44.563 --> 00:36:46.685
Yeah? Seem to you?

435
00:36:46.685 --> 00:36:48.599
It's a bit flashy.

436
00:36:48.599 --> 00:36:51.598
You are my boyfriend. How would it not work?

437
00:36:57.971 --> 00:36:59.396
It's a lot of pressure.

438
00:36:59.396 --> 00:37:01.335
I'm about to be even more famous,

439
00:37:01.335 --> 00:37:03.150
You better prepare for that.

440
00:37:03.150 --> 00:37:05.748
Aren't you sick of plaid shirts?

441
00:37:05.748 --> 00:37:07.542
Hey, isn't that Yoon Sol?

442
00:37:07.542 --> 00:37:09.214
I think so.

443
00:37:09.214 --> 00:37:10.239
It just can't be.

444
00:37:10.239 --> 00:37:12.288
It's me, come.

445
00:37:12.288 --> 00:37:14.018
I follow you on Instagram,

446
00:37:14.018 --> 00:37:16.292
but you didn't follow me.

447
00:37:16.292 --> 00:37:17.856
I will do it if you send me a message.

448
00:37:17.856 --> 00:37:21.120
Can we take a photo with you?

449
00:37:21.120 --> 00:37:23.356
- Clear.
- Thank you.

450
00:37:23.356 --> 00:37:25.254
- It's very good.
- Delicious.

451
00:37:25.254 --> 00:37:26.917
It's tasty, right?

452
00:37:29.853 --> 00:37:31.157
Hey,

453
00:37:31.157 --> 00:37:32.858
stop roasting and eat a little.

454
00:37:32.858 --> 00:37:34.611
I'm eating.

455
00:37:42.330 --> 00:37:46.158
You look better than you did a few days ago.

456
00:37:46.158 --> 00:37:48.356
Yes, you must be eating well.

457
00:37:48.356 --> 00:37:49.727
Eating well?

458
00:37:49.727 --> 00:37:52.258
No, it's because he doesn't have an annoying wife.

459
00:37:54.815 --> 00:37:56.925
There you are.

460
00:37:56.925 --> 00:37:59.118
- Our guide arrived.
- Hello!

461
00:37:59.935 --> 00:38:01.434
How good to see you.

462
00:38:01.434 --> 00:38:03.735
You're late, right?

463
00:38:03.735 --> 00:38:06.012
I'm late on purpose when I'm free.

464
00:38:06.012 --> 00:38:09.384
I'm tired of arriving early
and take care of everything.

465
00:38:10.605 --> 00:38:12.832
It seems like an eternity passed.

466
00:38:12.832 --> 00:38:15.337
How good to see you all.

467
00:38:15.337 --> 00:38:16.774
Very well, eat.

468
00:38:16.774 --> 00:38:18.763
- Let's toast.
- Clear.

469
00:38:20.073 --> 00:38:21.765
Health!

470
00:38:28.375 --> 00:38:30.602
The marriage you lose
will pay for the game, okay?

471
00:38:30.602 --> 00:38:32.353
- Sounds good.
- Wait,

472
00:38:32.353 --> 00:38:34.164
They're not even married.

473
00:38:34.164 --> 00:38:35.930
So what are they?

474
00:38:35.930 --> 00:38:38.517
- Losing team pays!
- Deal done.

475
00:38:40.283 --> 00:38:42.681
I haven't played in 20 years.

476
00:38:42.681 --> 00:38:46.568
Me neither.
It's been more than ten years for me.

477
00:38:46.568 --> 00:38:48.321
Wow,

478
00:38:48.321 --> 00:38:50.688
It looks like we'll pay for everything.

479
00:38:50.688 --> 00:38:52.381
Let's do the best we can.

480
00:39:24.238 --> 00:39:26.404
- Everything went well, right?
- Yes.

481
00:39:27.017 --> 00:39:28.284
Here it comes.

482
00:39:28.284 --> 00:39:29.613
Thank you, doctor.

483
00:39:29.613 --> 00:39:31.265
Both mother and baby are healthy.

484
00:39:31.265 --> 00:39:34.029
- Thank you.
- Thank you so much.

485
00:39:34.029 --> 00:39:36.435
- Thank you.
- We appreciate it very much.

486
00:40:13.921 --> 00:40:15.952
Why did you do that?

487
00:40:15.952 --> 00:40:19.031
- You should have told him before.
- I was going to do it,

488
00:40:20.324 --> 00:40:22.130
but you know.

489
00:40:22.984 --> 00:40:24.471
I

490
00:40:25.347 --> 00:40:26.940
and Jun Kyung...

491
00:40:28.967 --> 00:40:31.220
We only met a couple of times.

492
00:40:35.599 --> 00:40:37.372
In the store...

493
00:40:39.005 --> 00:40:40.812
when I gave him a ride...

494
00:40:44.522 --> 00:40:46.742
If I had told him: "I have a son..."

495
00:40:49.631 --> 00:40:51.817
I couldn't do that.

496
00:40:56.620 --> 00:40:59.026
And then we started dating...

497
00:41:03.166 --> 00:41:05.113
and I didn't know

498
00:41:06.639 --> 00:41:08.399
When to tell the truth.

499
00:41:11.312 --> 00:41:13.393
I know it all seems like an excuse, but...

500
00:41:13.393 --> 00:41:15.865
Yes, I understand.

501
00:41:15.865 --> 00:41:19.126
When he said we should go slow,

502
00:41:19.126 --> 00:41:20.763
I thought, "Okay,

503
00:41:20.763 --> 00:41:23.036
I will wait for the right moment."

504
00:41:25.121 --> 00:41:27.107
That's what I repeated to myself.

505
00:41:48.108 --> 00:41:49.508
Hey,

506
00:41:50.115 --> 00:41:51.974
you liked him a lot.

507
00:41:55.687 --> 00:41:56.711
So,

508
00:41:56.711 --> 00:41:59.111
Why don't you contact her again?

509
00:42:00.966 --> 00:42:02.519
We're done.

510
00:43:11.833 --> 00:43:13.573
Tell me.

511
00:43:14.900 --> 00:43:17.519
Let's hear your excuse.

512
00:43:41.329 --> 00:43:43.757
<i>At that moment,</i>

513
00:43:43.757 --> 00:43:45.563
<i>I realized.</i>

514
00:43:46.936 --> 00:43:51.362
<i>I like it a lot more than I thought.</i>

515
00:43:54.322 --> 00:43:57.216
<i>I am very sure of that.</i>

516
00:43:59.474 --> 00:44:02.313
<i>That's why I need to see it again.</i>

517
00:44:32.319 --> 00:44:33.919
When I was 20,

518
00:44:34.708 --> 00:44:36.114
It was very...

519
00:44:37.494 --> 00:44:39.394
immature

520
00:44:41.008 --> 00:44:42.420
Well...

521
00:44:44.114 --> 00:44:46.234
I still am a little.

522
00:44:49.800 --> 00:44:51.926
My ex-girlfriend called me...

523
00:44:54.560 --> 00:44:56.960
Two months after we broke up.

524
00:44:59.447 --> 00:45:02.800
She said she was pregnant.

525
00:45:06.796 --> 00:45:08.422
Suddenly...

526
00:45:12.849 --> 00:45:15.415
the idea of having a child...

527
00:45:17.541 --> 00:45:19.321
honestly...

528
00:45:22.861 --> 00:45:24.801
It scared me.

529
00:45:27.548 --> 00:45:29.615
As for

530
00:45:29.615 --> 00:45:31.348
I saw his face...

531
00:45:35.270 --> 00:45:37.116
I felt overwhelmed...

532
00:45:39.383 --> 00:45:41.356
and moved.

533
00:45:42.990 --> 00:45:44.390
I was...

534
00:45:46.030 --> 00:45:48.943
strangely moved.

535
00:45:49.729 --> 00:45:51.210
That's how I felt.

536
00:45:53.942 --> 00:45:55.902
but

537
00:45:55.902 --> 00:45:57.968
we were already done,

538
00:45:58.609 --> 00:46:00.715
and try to return

539
00:46:02.450 --> 00:46:04.850
just for responsibility...

540
00:46:07.329 --> 00:46:09.390
It wasn't possible.

541
00:46:11.724 --> 00:46:15.243
My ex took the baby
and went to Germany to study.

542
00:46:16.815 --> 00:46:18.755
We contacted again

543
00:46:20.028 --> 00:46:21.908
last year.

544
00:46:25.616 --> 00:46:27.376
my son

545
00:46:27.376 --> 00:46:29.476
He wanted to meet me.

546
00:46:31.715 --> 00:46:33.981
I wanted to live in Korea.

547
00:46:37.154 --> 00:46:38.674
So...

548
00:46:39.934 --> 00:46:42.740
after 14 years,

549
00:46:42.740 --> 00:46:44.440
I met him.

550
00:46:56.085 --> 00:46:57.918
What's it called?

551
00:47:06.467 --> 00:47:08.247
Daniel.

552
00:47:11.572 --> 00:47:13.199
Im Daniel.

553
00:47:14.326 --> 00:47:15.850
He is 15

554
00:47:16.457 --> 00:47:18.236
and it is very tall.

555
00:47:21.211 --> 00:47:23.551
He's in that cynical teenage phase, right?

556
00:47:26.340 --> 00:47:28.287
Yes,

557
00:47:28.287 --> 00:47:29.846
Exactly.

558
00:47:30.952 --> 00:47:33.605
That little boy...

559
00:47:36.220 --> 00:47:38.220
while growing up...

560
00:47:43.000 --> 00:47:45.359
I couldn't do anything for him.

561
00:47:50.113 --> 00:47:51.878
That is.

562
00:47:53.212 --> 00:47:55.005
That's my excuse.

563
00:47:56.332 --> 00:47:58.978
What I really wanted to tell you...

564
00:48:02.866 --> 00:48:04.745
no excuses...

565
00:48:07.662 --> 00:48:09.535
is that...

566
00:48:13.057 --> 00:48:16.070
I'm very sorry.

567
00:48:17.190 --> 00:48:19.223
I've already forgiven you.

568
00:48:22.923 --> 00:48:25.663
From the moment I saw your face
a while ago

569
00:48:40.515 --> 00:48:44.041
I have something I want to give you.

570
00:48:50.011 --> 00:48:52.111
Wait, you had this?

571
00:48:58.193 --> 00:49:00.245
If we hadn't finished,

572
00:49:01.139 --> 00:49:04.145
you would still listen to music
one-sided forever.

573
00:49:13.395 --> 00:49:15.496
Thanks to you,
We didn't have to pay for the game,

574
00:49:15.496 --> 00:49:17.503
But I feel bad for the others.

575
00:49:17.503 --> 00:49:21.096
You don't seem that sorry.
You tried so hard.

576
00:49:21.096 --> 00:49:23.594
I'm not usually competitive.

577
00:49:23.594 --> 00:49:25.937
but tonight I didn't want to lose.

578
00:49:25.937 --> 00:49:27.394
Oh really? Because?

579
00:49:27.394 --> 00:49:30.506
I don't mind losing alone,
but you would have lost too.

580
00:49:31.721 --> 00:49:34.466
- You're very kind.
- No, come on.

581
00:49:34.466 --> 00:49:36.514
I'm serious.

582
00:49:36.514 --> 00:49:39.087
You are tall for your age,

583
00:49:39.087 --> 00:49:41.422
You don't have a belly or anything.

584
00:49:41.422 --> 00:49:43.229
I'm holding her back right now.

585
00:49:43.916 --> 00:49:46.362
If you dyed your gray hair a little...

586
00:49:48.442 --> 00:49:50.862
Maybe you would look younger than me.

587
00:49:52.864 --> 00:49:54.733
You said it was ten years ago
that you didn't play bowling.

588
00:49:54.733 --> 00:49:56.329
How come you played so well?

589
00:49:56.329 --> 00:49:59.242
I try hard not to forget, that's all.

590
00:50:00.122 --> 00:50:04.156
When things are difficult,
I try to forget,

591
00:50:04.156 --> 00:50:06.636
and when things are good,

592
00:50:06.636 --> 00:50:08.447
I try not to do it.

593
00:50:08.447 --> 00:50:10.780
Does that work when you want it to?

594
00:50:13.465 --> 00:50:15.498
Are you curious?

595
00:50:15.498 --> 00:50:17.523
Is this okay?

596
00:50:17.523 --> 00:50:18.869
What thing?

597
00:50:18.869 --> 00:50:22.955
Let him come like this to see a woman who lives alone.

598
00:50:24.881 --> 00:50:26.775
you will not have

599
00:50:26.775 --> 00:50:29.541
Weird ideas, right?

600
00:50:29.541 --> 00:50:31.241
That?

601
00:50:31.241 --> 00:50:33.668
No, don't get me wrong.

602
00:50:57.231 --> 00:50:59.598
I got scared.

603
00:50:59.598 --> 00:51:01.939
This is Bom.

604
00:51:01.939 --> 00:51:03.373
Hello.

605
00:51:03.373 --> 00:51:05.816
- I didn't scare her, did I?
- Not at all.

606
00:51:05.816 --> 00:51:09.429
Did you have fun today? Greet him.

607
00:51:09.429 --> 00:51:12.309
This place used to be a pool hall.

608
00:51:12.309 --> 00:51:15.154
With my work and my personality,
I move a lot.

609
00:51:15.154 --> 00:51:18.169
I never needed a place
that felt like my home.

610
00:51:18.169 --> 00:51:21.189
A little unusual, isn't it?

611
00:51:22.253 --> 00:51:23.596
No,

612
00:51:23.596 --> 00:51:25.619
I think it's wonderful.

613
00:51:25.619 --> 00:51:27.426
It feels

614
00:51:27.426 --> 00:51:29.579
like a hiding place.

615
00:51:52.727 --> 00:51:54.553
You are a person...

616
00:51:56.840 --> 00:51:59.006
incredible.

617
00:52:02.089 --> 00:52:04.693
Some buy souvenirs,

618
00:52:04.693 --> 00:52:06.577
take photos

619
00:52:06.577 --> 00:52:09.159
and publish them on social networks,

620
00:52:09.159 --> 00:52:11.159
but me

621
00:52:11.159 --> 00:52:12.972
just drawing.

622
00:52:14.065 --> 00:52:15.930
I draw the things I want to remember,

623
00:52:15.930 --> 00:52:17.534
the things that I felt,

624
00:52:17.534 --> 00:52:20.505
the people I met
and the conversations we had,

625
00:52:20.505 --> 00:52:22.431
so as not to forget them.

626
00:52:23.867 --> 00:52:26.333
That's how I remember things.

627
00:52:29.613 --> 00:52:32.046
What do you want to remember now?

628
00:52:36.619 --> 00:52:38.439
Can I see it?

629
00:52:40.579 --> 00:52:42.752
- Yeah.
- Gracias.

630
00:52:50.210 --> 00:52:51.610
Vaya.

631
00:52:54.590 --> 00:52:57.396
He still has a lot to go.

632
00:53:24.469 --> 00:53:26.515
Are you really Seo Jun Seo?

633
00:53:27.235 --> 00:53:29.515
- That?
- What's that?

634
00:53:29.515 --> 00:53:31.682
Are they punishing you or something?

635
00:53:31.682 --> 00:53:33.889
- It doesn't suit me, does it?
- No not at all.

636
00:53:34.842 --> 00:53:36.629
Sol bought it for me.

637
00:53:37.261 --> 00:53:39.053
It doesn't suit you.

638
00:53:39.053 --> 00:53:40.979
I thought so too.

639
00:53:48.474 --> 00:53:51.441
Why do they go out if they don't even match?

640
00:53:53.168 --> 00:53:55.141
Because I like it.

641
00:53:55.141 --> 00:53:56.981
Because she's pretty, right?

642
00:53:57.945 --> 00:53:59.675
Well,

643
00:53:59.675 --> 00:54:01.052
It's great.

644
00:54:01.052 --> 00:54:03.702
He knows what he wants.

645
00:54:03.702 --> 00:54:05.955
It does everything well.

646
00:54:07.022 --> 00:54:10.409
Why would you like me,

647
00:54:10.409 --> 00:54:12.475
a loser?

648
00:54:13.589 --> 00:54:15.568
Why are you a loser?

649
00:54:17.666 --> 00:54:19.546
You're great too.

650
00:54:20.486 --> 00:54:22.106
Oh really?

651
00:54:22.746 --> 00:54:24.552
In what sense?

652
00:54:30.232 --> 00:54:32.175
She's always busy,

653
00:54:32.175 --> 00:54:34.758
It always makes you nervous.

654
00:54:34.758 --> 00:54:38.399
It is very thin,
I don't even think she's that pretty,

655
00:54:38.399 --> 00:54:40.659
but you are always on his side.

656
00:54:41.912 --> 00:54:44.818
Yeah, that's what makes you a cool guy.

657
00:54:50.924 --> 00:54:52.477
What are you doing?

658
00:54:52.477 --> 00:54:55.780
What does it matter if you think I'm cool?

659
00:54:55.780 --> 00:54:57.554
Sol is the one who should think that.

660
00:54:57.554 --> 00:54:59.660
Why can't it be me?

661
00:55:01.427 --> 00:55:03.367
Let's stop.

662
00:55:03.367 --> 00:55:05.114
See you later.

663
00:55:21.556 --> 00:55:23.209
Dad?

664
00:55:30.357 --> 00:55:34.524
A grandmother from my sister's town raised Bom.

665
00:55:35.489 --> 00:55:38.455
He passed away, and Bom was left alone.

666
00:55:38.455 --> 00:55:39.969
That's horrible.

667
00:55:39.969 --> 00:55:43.375
I felt alone, so I took her in,

668
00:55:44.069 --> 00:55:48.262
but more time passes
in the nursery than with me.

669
00:55:48.262 --> 00:55:50.449
I tell myself I'm busy,

670
00:55:50.449 --> 00:55:52.889
and I think that makes her feel alone.

671
00:55:56.984 --> 00:56:00.530
Is the man in the drawing your husband?

672
00:56:01.417 --> 00:56:03.074
Never!

673
00:56:03.074 --> 00:56:05.760
No? What a relief.

674
00:56:06.944 --> 00:56:09.967
It was part of a couples tour

675
00:56:09.967 --> 00:56:11.858
and he wouldn't stop flirting with me.

676
00:56:11.858 --> 00:56:16.530
His wife was there. What was I thinking?

677
00:56:16.530 --> 00:56:19.220
It was a cruise ship, so there was no escape.

678
00:56:19.220 --> 00:56:23.197
It was very uncomfortable and annoying.

679
00:56:23.197 --> 00:56:26.417
I drew him to curse him for life.

680
00:56:26.417 --> 00:56:27.667
That?

681
00:56:27.667 --> 00:56:29.772
That guy is an idiot.

682
00:56:29.772 --> 00:56:33.157
Married and disgusting, seriously.

683
00:56:34.157 --> 00:56:35.641
Do you curse too?

684
00:56:35.641 --> 00:56:37.912
Anyone with common sense would do it.

685
00:56:37.912 --> 00:56:39.723
He's a damn.

686
00:56:49.224 --> 00:56:50.855
- You can answer.
- OK.

687
00:56:50.855 --> 00:56:53.568
[My son]

688
00:56:55.348 --> 00:56:57.202
Hello, Jun Seo.

689
00:56:57.202 --> 00:56:58.227
That?

690
00:56:58.227 --> 00:57:00.456
Is it already that late?

691
00:57:00.456 --> 00:57:01.546
Yes.

692
00:57:01.546 --> 00:57:04.307
I'm just with some friends.

693
00:57:04.307 --> 00:57:07.956
OK. I'll be home soon, don't worry.

694
00:57:07.956 --> 00:57:09.942
I'm coming.

695
00:57:09.942 --> 00:57:11.789
I said I'm on my way.

696
00:57:11.789 --> 00:57:13.355
Bye bye.

697
00:57:17.867 --> 00:57:19.967
You should go home.

698
00:57:23.767 --> 00:57:25.167
Yes.

699
00:57:27.113 --> 00:57:29.652
There are no more drinks anyway.

700
00:57:29.652 --> 00:57:31.893
and it's too late.

701
00:57:49.770 --> 00:57:51.170
Hey, Boom...

702
00:57:53.658 --> 00:57:55.358
I'm leaving

703
00:57:55.358 --> 00:57:58.537
I hope we can see each other again.

704
00:57:58.537 --> 00:58:00.151
Take care of yourself.

705
00:58:02.305 --> 00:58:04.244
Leave.

706
00:58:05.094 --> 00:58:07.007
Do you want to stay the night?

707
00:58:39.799 --> 00:58:41.939
Weren't you going home?

708
00:58:42.785 --> 00:58:45.292
I felt like I needed another drink,

709
00:58:46.419 --> 00:58:48.905
so I stopped by the store.

710
00:58:51.302 --> 00:58:52.741
Seriously...

711
00:58:55.154 --> 00:58:56.977
can I stay the night?

712
00:59:38.141 --> 00:59:41.544
<i>- Don't you have a boyfriend?
- Yes, but it's not good for Sol.</i>

713
00:59:41.544 --> 00:59:44.025
<i>He's a graduate loser,</i>

714
00:59:44.025 --> 00:59:46.265
<i>so I would try it.</i>

715
00:59:46.265 --> 00:59:48.964
<i>- I want to say it's love, but...
- Call the police!</i>

716
00:59:48.964 --> 00:59:51.631
<i>Do you think I will be in Sol's future?</i>

717
00:59:52.275 --> 00:59:55.426
<i>I was afraid that people would notice</i>

718
00:59:55.426 --> 00:59:57.033
<i>how much I like you.</i>

719
00:59:57.033 --> 00:59:59.016
<i>Do you really think that Julia</i>

720
00:59:59.016 --> 01:00:00.879
<i>would I want to see you punish yourself like this?</i>

721
01:00:00.879 --> 01:00:02.710
<i>You don't have to blame yourself.</i>

722
01:00:02.710 --> 01:00:05.975
<i>I'm tired of worrying
for what others think.</i>

723
01:00:06.822 --> 01:00:08.479
<i>Dad?</i>

724
01:00:08.479 --> 01:00:10.412
<i>What was that?</i>

725
01:00:10.412 --> 01:00:11.796
<i>Hello.</i>

726
01:00:11.796 --> 01:00:15.286
<i>Daniel, I want you to meet my girlfriend.</i>

727
01:00:15.286 --> 01:00:16.884
<i>Are you cooking? That's new.</i>

728
01:00:16.884 --> 01:00:19.644
<i>Why are you so nice to him?</i>

729
01:00:20.456 --> 01:00:22.203
<i>She's crazy.</i>

730
01:00:23.010 --> 01:00:25.166
<i>I'm sorry, Jun Kyung.</i>

731
01:00:25.166 --> 01:00:27.776
<i>What? Have they already left you?</i>

